   "source": [
    "## 3. Calibration Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "We compare three approaches:\n",
    "- **Uncalibrated**: Raw ensemble probabilities (XGBoost + LightGBM average)\n",
    "- **Platt Scaling (Sigmoid)**: Fits a logistic regression on model output — best for monotonic distortions\n",
    "- **Isotonic Regression**: Non-parametric — more flexible but can overfit with small datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "A well-calibrated model means: when it says \"70% chance\", the event happens ~70% of the time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "ss7f1x9s2d",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-10T22:56:27.226558Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-03-10T22:56:27.226427Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-03-10T22:56:29.921284Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-03-10T22:56:29.919925Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Calibration models trained.\n",
      "  XGB + Platt:  Brier = 0.2093\n",
      "  XGB + Iso:    Brier = 0.2055\n",
      "  Cal Ensemble: Brier = 0.2064\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Train calibrated versions of XGBoost\n",
    "cal_sigmoid = CalibratedClassifierCV(xgb_clf, method=\"sigmoid\", cv=5)\n",
    "cal_sigmoid.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "cal_isotonic = CalibratedClassifierCV(xgb_clf, method=\"isotonic\", cv=5)\n",
    "cal_isotonic.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get calibrated probabilities\n",
    "sigmoid_probs = cal_sigmoid.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "isotonic_probs = cal_isotonic.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calibrate the full ensemble using Platt scaling on XGBoost\n",
    "# (Simpler and avoids sklearn classifier detection issues with custom wrappers)\n",
    "# We manually average calibrated XGB + raw LGBM for the ensemble calibration\n",
    "cal_xgb_for_ens = CalibratedClassifierCV(xgb_clf, method=\"sigmoid\", cv=5)\n",
    "cal_xgb_for_ens.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "cal_xgb_probs = cal_xgb_for_ens.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "cal_lgbm_for_ens = CalibratedClassifierCV(lgbm_clf, method=\"sigmoid\", cv=5)\n",
    "cal_lgbm_for_ens.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "cal_lgbm_probs = cal_lgbm_for_ens.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calibrated ensemble = average of individually calibrated models\n",
    "cal_ens_probs = (cal_xgb_probs + cal_lgbm_probs) / 2\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Calibration models trained.\")\n",
    "print(f\"  XGB + Platt:  Brier = {brier_score_loss(y_test, sigmoid_probs):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  XGB + Iso:    Brier = {brier_score_loss(y_test, isotonic_probs):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Cal Ensemble: Brier = {brier_score_loss(y_test, cal_ens_probs):.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
