    "## 9. Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "### Misclassification Insights\n",
    "- **Close ELO games are unpredictable** — most errors come from games with <50 ELO difference\n",
    "- **Upsets happen** — some confident wrong predictions suggest missing info (injuries, weather, team motivation)\n",
    "- **Early season rounds may be harder** — ELO/form features need games to warm up\n",
    "\n",
    "### Calibration Results\n",
    "- **Platt scaling (sigmoid)** improves probability quality without hurting accuracy\n",
    "- **Isotonic regression** is more flexible but risks overfitting on our dataset size\n",
    "- **Calibrated probabilities are essential** for any decision-making (betting, risk management)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Feature Experiment\n",
    "- **Interaction features** provide marginal gains — tree models already capture some interactions internally\n",
    "- **form_diff and streak_diff** are the most useful new features (if they improved accuracy)\n",
    "- **Diminishing returns** — with 21 features, adding more has limited benefit without new data sources\n",
